y-packed debris cloud or a particle breaking up due to\nelectrostatic fragmentation after high charging.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 13 Sep 2006 01:19:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2007-05-23"}
{"id":"astro-ph/0609342","submitter":"Leonid Malyshkin","authors":"Leonid Malyshkin and Russell M. Kulsrud","title":"On the two-dimensional magnetic reconnection with nonuniform resistivity","comments":"7 pages, 1 figure","journal-ref":"Phys.Scripta T142: 014034,2010","doi":"10.1088/0031-8949/2010/T142/014034","report-no":null,"categories":"astro-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  In this paper two theoretical approaches for the calculation of the rate of\nquasi-stationary, two-dimensional magnetic reconnection with nonuniform\nanomalous resistivity are considered in the framework of incompressible\nmagnetohydrodynamics (MHD). In the first, ``global'' equations approach the MHD\nequations are approximately solved for a whole reconnection layer, including\nthe upstream and downstream regions and the layer center. In the second,\n``local'' equations approach the equations are solved across the reconnection\nlayer, including only the upstream region and the layer center. Both approaches\ngive the same approximate answer for the reconnection rate. Our theoretical\nmodel is in agreement with the results of recent simulations of reconnection\nwith spatially nonuniform resistivity by Baty, Priest and Forbes (2006),\ncontrary to their conclusions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 13 Sep 2006 02:36:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 16 Oct 2008 19:04:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-24"}
