axies the $B/T$ flux ratio is as small as in\ntypical Sc-type spirals. This might be the hitherto undiscovered link in the\nscenario in which spirals are transformedinto S0s. Also, bars in S0s are found\nto be shorter and less massive, and have smaller bar torques than bars in\nS0/a-type galaxies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 13 Sep 2006 11:17:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-11"}
